
@startuml

class Song {
  -title: String
  -year: Integer
  -length: Integer
  -genre: String
  -trackNumber: Integer
  +getDetails(): String
}

class Artist {
  -name: String
  -dateOfBirth: Date
  -url: String
  +getName(): String
}

class User {
  -id: Integer
  -name: String
  -address: String
  +getId(): Integer
  +getName(): String
  +getAddress(): String
}

class RegularUser <|-- User {
  +buySong(song: Song): void
  +buyAlbum(album: Album): void
}

class BusinessUser <|-- User {
  -vatNumber: String
  +uploadSong(song: Song): void
}

class Album {
  -title: String
  -releaseYear: Integer
  +getTitle(): String
  +getReleaseYear(): Integer
}

class Hit <|-- Song {
  -album: Album
  +addToAlbum(album: Album, trackNumber: Integer): void
}

class Single <|-- Song {
  +getTrackNumber(): Integer
}

class Suggestion {
  -user: User
  -recommendedAlbums: List<Album>
  +generateSuggestions(user: User): void
}

Song "1" -- "1" Artist : belongs to
Hit "1" --> "1" Album : part of
Single "0..*" --> "1" Album : part of (optional)
BusinessUser "1" --> "0..*" Single : uploads
RegularUser "1" --> "0..*" Single : buys
RegularUser "1" --> "0..*" Album : buys
User "1" --> "0..*" Suggestion : receives

@enduml

---

### 🔍 Explanation of Key Relationships and Features:

- **Song** is a base class with attributes like `title`, `year`, `length`, and `genre`.
- **Artist** has unique name and associated metadata.
- **User** is the base class for both **RegularUser** and **BusinessUser**.
- **BusinessUser** has an additional `vatNumber` attribute and can upload songs.
- **RegularUser** can buy singles or albums.
- **Songs** are classified into two types:
  - **Single**: Can be bought directly by regular users.
  - **Hit**: Part of an **Album**, which consists of multiple hits. The position of each hit in the album is stored as `trackNumber`.
- **Albums** can be used to suggest similar content to other users.
- A **Suggestion** class represents recommendations generated based on user behavior.

